ABOUT ME

As a self-taught product designer with 9+ years of experience, I bring a unique perspective to the design process. My skills are centered around human-computer interactions, allow me to create delightful experiences that solve complex problems.

I can take an idea to concept to wireframe to prototype to development.

Lead Product Designer

Classplus

Feb 2022 - Present

As the Lead Product Designer at Classplus, a leading B2B ed-tech company, I drive the end-to-end user experience strategy across our extensive suite of products. Starting as a Senior Product Designer, I’ve grown into a leadership role where I spearhead the design efforts to enhance usability, accessibility, and visual consistency at scale through a robust, cross-platform design system.

During my tenure, Classplus has expanded its footprint by acquiring Testbook and launching multiple ventures including Polaris, Plutus, and The Legal School. I have played a pivotal role in shaping the product design direction for all these entities, ensuring a cohesive user experience across diverse user groups and business models. My responsibilities include:

  • Leading cross-functional design initiatives across multiple product teams

  • Building and maintaining a scalable design system for consistency and efficiency

  • Driving UX strategy and accessibility standards across all platforms

  • Collaborating closely with stakeholders to align business goals with user needs

  • Mentoring and upskilling design team members to foster growth and innovation
